transliteration: Disaamaaoun Aaianidait Raajan|| Bhaje Sarab Devan Taje Sarab Saajan||
translation: More forces of demons came from another direction, seeing which the gods, leaving all their paraphernalia, ran away.

translation: The limbs began to fall in great numbers and the arrows looked auspicious in the manner of the flowers of capparis in the month of the Chaitra.19.

transliteration: Sure Jan Haariyo Keeyo Bisan Mantran|| Bhayo Antra Dhyaanan Daryo Jaan Tantran||
translation: The gods were defeated in the war and Vishnu, thinking over it disappeared, with the help of Tantric science.

gurmukhi: mhwN mohnI rUp DwrXo AnUpM ]Cky dyiK doaU id`iqXwid`iq BUpM ]
transliteration: Mahaan Mohaniroop Dhdaryo Anoopan|| Chhake Dekh(i) Dooo Dittiyaaditt(i) Bhoopan||20||
translation: Then he manifested himself in the unique form of Maha-Mohini, seeing whom, the chief of the demons and gods were highly pleased.20.

gurmukhi: ieiq sRI bicqR nwtk gRMQy nr qiRqIX Aqy nwrwiex cqurQ Avqwr sMpUrnM ]3]4]
transliteration: It(i) Sribachitra Naatak Granthe Nar Triteeyaa Ate Naaraain Chaturath Avtaar Sanpooranan||3||4||
translation: End of the description of the third incarnation of NAR and the fourth incarnation of NARAYAN in BACHITTAR NATAK.3.4.
Now begins the description of Maha Mohini Incarnation:
Let Sri Bhagauti Ji (The Primal Lord) be helpful.
Vishnu transformed himself into form of Maha Mohini;
Seeing which both and the demons were allured.

gurmukhi: Cky pRym jogM rhy rIJ srbM ]
transliteration: Chhake Prem Jouang Rahe Reejh Saraban||
translation: All of them wanted to please her and thought of sharing her love;
